<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-03T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4280: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-03T21:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 3,
                                        1922—9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 6—11:45
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>128. Following telegram has been received from Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>March 30, 5 p.m. Fifty-two cars Fengtien troops from railway zone
                                    will leave Harbin today at 6:10 p.m. for Changchun. Expected 15
                                    or 20 additional troop trains will be sent south within next two
                                    weeks. Rumored in Harbin over-issue bank Three Provinces notes
                                    will be made finance campaign.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>